The '''bare-eyed myna''' ('''''Streptocitta albertinae''''') is a large, long-tailed species of [[starling]] in the family [[Sturnidae]]. Its [[common name]] is a reference to the large patch of dark bare skin around the eyes. Due to its superficial resemblance to a [[Pica (bird)|magpie]], it has been referred to as the '''Sula magpie''' in the past. It is [[endemic]] to [[tropical]] open [[lowland]] forests on the [[Indonesia]]n islands of [[Taliabu Island Regency|Taliabu]] and [[Mangole Island|Mangole]] in the [[Sula Islands Regency|Sula Islands]]. It is threatened by [[habitat loss]].

